Grammar of graphics

Mahbubul Majumder, PhD
Feb 9, 2017

What is grammar of graphics

  • describes the deep features that underlie all statistical graphics

  • an answer to a question: what is a statistical graphic?

  • according to Hadley Wickham

    The grammar tells us that a statistical graphic is a mapping from data to aesthetic attributes (colour, shape, size) of geometric objects (points, lines, bars).

Why do we need a grammar of graphics

  • similar to asking why we need a grammar

    • the fundamental principles or rules of an art or science

  • consistency of plots

  • it allows

    • extension of a graphics without changing much
    • switch between geometries of the plot without complexity
    • complex graphics to be generated in less effort
    • restrictions to make common mistakes

    • easy reproducibility

How the grammar works

Note: One variable could be mapped to multiple aesthetics

Data mapping

  • The trt column is mapped with aesthetic colour
  • Length and width are mapped with aesthetics x and y

Data scaling

  • The pixel of graphics could be different from actual data
    • The axis scales are done based on the coordinate system
  • The scale of data needs to be changed for convenient shape of the plot

Making the plot

The final plot

Component of data graphics

  • Data
  • Geometric object (geom)
  • Statistical transformation (stat)
  • Scales
  • Coordinate system
  • (+ Position adjustment, faceting)
  • example
    • geom: histogram
    • stat: bin
    • scale: linear
    • Coordinate: Cartesian

ggplot2: an implementation in R

tips <- read.csv("http://www.ggobi.org/book/data/tips.csv")
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(tips, aes(tip)) + geom_histogram(binwidth=0.5)

Layered grammar

  • Adding layer
ggplot(tips,
       aes(totbill,tip)) +
  geom_point()


ggplot(tips,
       aes(totbill,tip)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method="lm", se=F)

Faceting

ggplot(tips, aes(totbill,tip)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method="lm", se=F) +
  facet_grid(sex~smoker)

Legend and labels

Legend and labels

ggplot(tips, aes(factor(size),tip,color=factor(size))) + 
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=factor(size)), alpha=0.3) +
  xlab("Party size") +
  theme(legend.position = "none")

How many layers?

Construction of a layer

layer(
 data = mpg,
 mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy),
 geom = "point",
 stat = "identity",
 position = "identity"
)
  • example layers
    • geom_point()
    • geom_smooth()

geom and stat

Facet wrap vs grid

  • facet_grid(v1~v2)
  • facet_grid(.~v2)
  • facet_wrap(~v1, ncol=2)
